Today, now, for the benefit of some of our listeners, I want to talk about control of undesirable hardwoods.
As you may or may not know, those poor quality hardwood trees growing in your pine woods are costing you a lot of money.
Now, it may sound a little odd to you that today we're telling you to get rid of trees.
Well, usually we tell you to plant more of them.
Just as it's important for you to keep fire out of the woods, it's also important for you to keep those wolf trees out of your pines.
And if you are to make the most profit from them, I've got some good advice for you.

Friends, I guess about the best way for you to get rid of those small, undesirable trees of yours is to use the chemical known as 245T.

Now, the district foresters of the Texas Forest Service have set up several demonstration areas in order to help you solve your undesirable hardwood problems and to test the effectiveness of different methods of control.
And here's what they say is all you have to do.
Mix up a solution of one gallon of 245T to 20 gallons of diesel oil and simply spray it all around the base of the tree and up the trunk for about two feet.
And be sure the bark is saturated.
This is recommended only for trees eight inches or less to prevent sprouting.
Now on trees above this size, girdling alone will generally suffice.
A single hack girdle around the trunk of the tree, in which a solution of 245T is used, is also very effective.
And that's all there is to it.
The kill is very quick, and in a few days' time most trees will start to wilt.
A few species, like hickory, die more slowly, but usually one application is all that's required to kill any tree.
It doesn't affect the spray in any way, but it will make your work easier if you add a little red stain to the solution when you mix it up.
You see, after a few days' time, the oil is pretty well soaked into the bark, and it's hard to see which tree has been sprayed or not.
245T can be purchased from garden stores or chemical houses.
Your district forester will be able to advise you on the use of it or on other methods of controlling your undesirable hardwoods.
